\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl1
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What it does:
\f1\b0  The ultimate hardware gatekeeper. No matter what the Pi or the user requests, this function decides where the servo actually goes.\
\ls8\ilvl1
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 How it works:
\f1\b0  1. It compares the requested angle against 
\f3\fs26 ABS_MIN_LEFT
\f1\fs24  and 
\f3\fs26 ABS_MAX_RIGHT
\f1\fs24 . If the request exceeds these walls, it clamps the value. 2. It has a hardcoded secondary clamp (
\f3\fs26 50.0
\f1\fs24  and 
\f3\fs26 130.0
\f1\fs24 ) to prevent EEPROM corruption from destroying the servo. 3. It converts the 0-180 degree angle into precise Microsecond pulses (
\f3\fs26 544 + (int)(angle * 10.3111)
\f1\fs24 ) for high-resolution servo control.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

